016package edu.cnm.deepdive.teamle.model.entity;
017
018import androidx.annotation.NonNull;
019import androidx.annotation.Nullable;
020import androidx.room.ColumnInfo;
021import androidx.room.Entity;
022import androidx.room.Index;
023import androidx.room.PrimaryKey;
024import java.time.Instant;
025
026/**
027 * Encapsulates the data elements maintained for a signed-in user in the app's Room/SQLite-based
028 * persistent data store.
029 */
030@SuppressWarnings("unused")
031@Entity(
032    tableName = "user",
033    indices = {
034        @Index(value = "oauth_key", unique = true),
035        @Index(value = "display_name", unique = true)
036    }
037)
038public class User {
039
040  @PrimaryKey(autoGenerate = true)
041  @ColumnInfo(name = "user_id")
042  private long id;
043
044  @NonNull
045  private Instant created = Instant.MIN;
046
047  @ColumnInfo(name = "oauth_key")
048  @NonNull
049  private String oauthKey = "";
050
051  @ColumnInfo(name = "display_name", collate = ColumnInfo.NOCASE)
052  @NonNull
053  private String displayName = "";
054
055  // TODO Define additional fields as appropriate.
056
057  /**
058   * Returns the auto-generated unique identifier of this instance.
059   */
060  public long getId() {
061    return id;
062  }
063
064  /**
065   * Sets the unique identifier of this instance.
066   *
067   * @param id
068   */
069  @SuppressWarnings("JavadocDeclaration")
070  public void setId(long id) {
071    this.id = id;
072  }
073
074  /**
075   * Returns the timestamp of the INSERT of this user in the database.
076   */
077  @NonNull
078  public Instant getCreated() {
079    return created;
080  }
081
082  /**
083   * Sets the INSERT timestamp of this user. This method should be invoked just prior to INSERT.
084   *
085   * @param created
086   */
087  @SuppressWarnings("JavadocDeclaration")
088  public void setCreated(@NonNull Instant created) {
089    this.created = created;
090  }
091
092  /**
093   * Returns the fixed OAuth2.0 identifier (aka <em>subject</em>) of this user.
094   */
095  @NonNull
096  public String getOauthKey() {
097    return oauthKey;
098  }
099
100  /**
101   * Sets the fixed OAuth2.0 identifier (aka <em>subject</em>) of this user.
102   *
103   * @param oauthKey
104   */
105  @SuppressWarnings("JavadocDeclaration")
106  public void setOauthKey(@NonNull String oauthKey) {
107    this.oauthKey = oauthKey;
108  }
109
110  /**
111   * Returns unique display name of this user.
112   */
113  @NonNull
114  public String getDisplayName() {
115    return displayName;
116  }
117
118  /**
119   * Sets unique display name of this user.
120   *
121   * @param displayName
122   */
123  @SuppressWarnings("JavadocDeclaration")
124  public void setDisplayName(@NonNull String displayName) {
125    this.displayName = displayName;
126  }
127
128  // TODO Define additional getters and setters. These must be defined for any additional fields
129  //  mapped to database columns.
130
131  /**
132   * Computes and returns the {@code int}-valued hash code of this instance. Currently, this
133   * computation is based only on the primary key value.
134   */
135  @Override
136  public int hashCode() {
137    return Long.hashCode(id);
138  }
139
140  /**
141   * Compares this instance to {@code obj} for equality and returns a {@code boolean} result.
142   * Currently, this comparison is based only on the type of {@code obj}, and (if
143   * {@code obj instanceof User}) the primary key values of {@code this} and {@code (User) obj}: two
144   * instances of {@link User} are considered equal if and only if their {@code id} field values are
145   * equal and non-zero.
146   *
147   * @param obj Object to compared to {@code this}.
148   * @return {@code true} if {@code this} and {@code obj} should be considered equal; {@code false}
149   * otherwise.
150   */
151  @Override
152  public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj) {
153    boolean matched;
154    if (obj == this) {
155      matched = true;
156    } else if (obj instanceof User) {
157      User other = (User) obj;
158      matched = (id != 0 && other.id != 0 && id == other.id);
159    } else {
160      matched = false;
161    }
162    return matched;
163  }
164
165}
